A man was on Thursday charged with putting on a military jersey with the intentions of committing an offence. Denis Wahema denied the charges before Kibera senior principal magistrate Barbara Ojoo. He is accused of committing the offence in Lang'ata, Nairobi county.Â  He was also charged with possession of a toy pistol. According to a police report filed in court, Wahema was strolling along the railway line dressed in the military combat jacket. He ran away after seeing the police. The officers then pursued him and arrested him after firing in the air. Wahema pleaded with the court for lenient bond terms. He was released on Sh50,000 bond or Sh30,000 bail. The case will be mentioned on November 21 and heard on December 4. Edited by R.Wamochie